summary: I'm on an All Too Well binge and honestly I am feeling so many emotions.
body:
I’m on an All Too Well binge and honestly I am feeling so many emotions.

When I first heard it I’d gone through a really rough break up and I was broken. This song helped me realise I wasn’t alone and other people have survived this pain. I ended up back with that guy, he was emotionally abusive and I suffered for years. Now this song means recovery to me. It means that the memories stay with us but that he will never be able to forget what he did to me. He will be haunted by the memory of the girl he loved and how he ruined her. And I will be reminded of how I survived and will never let that happen to me ever again. Because I will always be the one real thing he ever knew. Thank you @taylorswift, recovering from bad relationships is never easy, it haunts me every day, but having an anthem to put on that speaks to my soul makes me feel like I can get through this

summary: In End Game when Taylor says “And I bury hatchets but I keep maps of where I put ‘em” she means that although she was ready for...
body:
In End Game when Taylor says “And I bury hatchets but I keep maps of where I put ‘em” she means that although she was ready for a fight she backs downs and forgives instead but she also never forgets what happened.

But, in the Elle essay when Taylor says “Step into the daylight and let it go”, she is essentially letting go of all that negativity that she held onto. 

Taylor is living a life of progression and learning, and that is one more lesson I take out of this.
